Time Inc. Atlantic Recording Company and Elektra Entertainment Records
Time, inc.
MS 3009-RG 51
4 Linear feet in 4 record cartons
1964-1993 (bulk, 1974-1993) Atlantic Recording Corporation and Elektra Entertainment are record labels which became known for certain genres of music and were both acquired by Warner Brothers and after the latter's merger with Time Inc. were managed under the Time Warner Entertainment division. The collection contains print-outs of sales data for artists signed with both labels. These materials are stored offsite and advance notice is required for use. Please contact manuscripts@nyhistory.org prior to your research visit to coordinate access. Keep in mind that it will take up to five (5) business days for collections to arrive, and you should plan your research accordingly.
Conditions Governing Access
Materials are stored offsite and advance notice is required for use. Please contact manuscripts@nyhistory.org prior to your research visit to coordinate access. Keep in mind that it will take between two (2) and five (5) business days for collections to arrive, and you should plan your research accordingly.
Open to qualified researchers with the exception of restricted materials. Restricted materials include contracts and are located in box R86.
Arrangement
The collection is arranged alphabetically based on the original arrangement.
Historical Note
Atlantic Recording Corporation (usually known as Atlantic Records) was a record label founded by Ahmet Ertegun and Herb Abramson in 1947 which became known for specializing in the jazz, R&B, and soul genres. In 1967, Atlantic Records was purchased by Warner Brothers.
Elektra Entertainment was a record label founded by by Jac Holzman and Paul Rickolt in 1950 which became known for releases in the rock and contemporary folk genres. Elektra was purchased in 1970 by Kinney National Services in 1970 which changed its name to Warner Communications in 1972.
In 1990 Warner Communications merged with Time Inc. to form Time Warner. In 1993 Time Warner Entertainment was formed as a division of the company which included music labels such as Atlantic Records and Elektra Entertainment.

Provenance
Gift of Time Inc. in 2015.
Preferred Citation
This record group should be cited as Time Inc. Atlantic Recording Company and Elektra Entertainment Records, MS 3009-RG 51, New-York Historical Society.
Processing Information
The Time Inc. Atlantic Recording Company and Elektra Entertainment Records were processed by Allen Thomas in 2020. The original folders were retained although some documents were transferred to archival containers in instances of overcrowding. Generic binders were disassembled and not retained, and their contents rehoused. Allen Thomas created the inventory and other descriptive notes to produce this finding aid.
Related Materials
This finding aid relates to just one record group of the Time Inc. Records. For information about the other record groups and for overall information about the archives, please see the Guide to the Time Inc. Records (MS 3009). The Henry Luce Papers (MS 3014) were acquired with the Time Inc. Records. The collection of books acquired with the records are cataloged as the Time Inc. Reference Library.
Scope and Contents
The collection consists of data print-outs listing artists signed with Atlantic Records and Elektra Entertainment with sales figures for releases for certain periods of time as well as a binder of information on the gathering of this matertial.
Conditions Governing Use
Photocopying undertaken by staff only. Limited to 20 exposures of stable, unbound material per day.
